  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Regional Saving Lives in the Caribbean Through Preparedness</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The ARC has been active in the Caribbean Region for a number of years working alongside Red Cross partners to implement resilience, health, and preparedness programs; risk reduction initiatives; and disaster response and recovery efforts. This project is a new initiative under way to introduce new technologies for communicating with the public about disaster risk in the Caribbean for preparedness, early warning, and response.  It aims to save lives and protect livelihoods and assets, increasing the impact of humanitarian efforts through low-cost means of reaching scale, and informing and empowering community decision-making on disaster management.  This 12-month regional initiative is funded by the United States Agency for International Development&#x2019;s Office of Foreign Disaster Assistance (OFDA).</narrative>
  </description>
